  "prompt": "How do you calculate the height of the mountains?",
  "response": "There are several methods to calculate the height of mountains:\n\n1. Topographic Surveys\n- Use surveying equipment like theodolites\n- Measure elevation from sea level\n- Precise but time-consuming\n\n2. Barometric Altimeters\n- Measure atmospheric pressure\n- Convert pressure differences to altitude\n- Used by hikers and mountaineers\n\n3. GPS Technology\n- Global Positioning System satellites\n- Provide precise elevation measurements\n- Accurate and quick method\n\n4. Satellite Radar Interferometry\n- Use satellite radar to measure terrain elevation\n- High-resolution topographic mapping\n- Covers large areas efficiently\n\n5. Trigonometric Calculations\n- Use triangulation techniques\n- Measure angles and distances\n- Traditional mathematical method\n\n6. Digital Elevation Models (DEMs)\n- Computer-generated terrain models\n- Combine satellite imagery and ground data\n- Provide detailed elevation information\n\n7. Aerial Photogrammetry\n- Use aerial photographs\n- Create 3D terrain models\n- Useful for mapping mountain ranges\n\nEach method has different levels of accuracy and is suitable for different scenarios and scales of measurement.",
